Exercise 13.54: What would happen if we defined a HasPtr moveassignment
operator but did not change the copy-and-swap operator? Write
code to test your answer.

Answer:
When using std::move the compiler will have multiple functions that fit and so we will have ambiguous function call.


Exercise 13.55: Add an rvalue reference version of push_back to your
StrBlob.

Answer:
void push_back(std::string&& s) {data->push_back(std::move(s));}

Exercise 13.56: What would happen if we defined sorted as:

Foo Foo::sorted() const & {
    Foo ret(*this);
    return ret.sorted();
}
Answer:
Defining sorted as above will cause an endless recursion since ret is a lvalue the version of
sorted that will be called will not be sorted()&& as expected but sorted() const & and so the code
will get stuck in an endless loop.

Exercise 13.57: What if we defined sorted as:

Foo Foo::sorted() const &
{
    return Foo(*this).sorted();
}
Answer:
Foo(*this) will return a rvalue so the version that will be called is sorted() &&.